    "121550877": {
      "title": "On the defect of compactness for the Strichartz estimates of the Schr\u00f6dinger equations",
      "abstract": "In this paper, we prove that every sequence of solutions to the linear Schrodinger equation, with bounded data in H1(Rd), d\u2a7e3, can be written, up to a subsequence, as an almost orthogonal sum of sequences of the type h\u2212(d\u22122)/2nV((t\u2212tn)/h2n, (x\u2212xn)/ hn ), where V is a solution of the linear Schrodinger equation, with a small remainder term in Strichartz norms. Using this decomposition, we prove a similar one for the defocusing H1-critical nonlinear Schrodinger equation, assuming that the initial data belong to a ball in the energy space where the equation is solvable. This implies, in particular, the existence of an a priori estimate of the Strichartz norms in terms of the energy."
    }
